owl:Ontology.terms:description: UOMO (User Oriented social Media Ontology) is an ontology for describing the information about Social Media focusing on the User Perspective.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: UOMO User Oriented social Media Ontology

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: additionalType

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: disambiguatingDescription

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: globalLocationNumber

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See background notes for more details.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: identifier

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: image

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: sameAs

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: It is intended both as the type of University or school general study program
It is intended for every kind of educational certificates (School diploma or Proof)

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: With automatic it is meant that the container is generated automatically by inference of the Social Media itself (such as the "Comments" and "Post" containers of Reddit) and that the user cannot directly modify it (like you can in Facebook)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Place

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The most generic type of item.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Thing

owl:Class.terms:description: The order is given through a generally unknown internal algorithm of the Social Media
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Algorithmic Order

owl:Class.terms:description: Color palette is intended as the range of colors that can be applied to general elements of the profile such as texts, containers or the background.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Color Palette

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A container is intended as a section of a profile that contains other elements such has media, hyperlinks, tags

owl:Class.terms:description: The order through which the items in a container are displayed
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Displaying Order

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: With Highlighted Media it is meant the main media that is displayed in a part of the profile which is not the background or the profile pic. As an example we have the main video played when you enter a Youtube channel or the Twitch stream in a Twitch profile. Note that both these Social Media have a Profile Picture.
A Network Container is intended as a particular kind of container that aggregates other social media profile under specific relationships (such as "following", "followers" etc...)

owl:Class.terms:description: The identifier of a user in a Social Media
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Account Name
Nickname

owl:Thing.terms:description: UOMO (User Oriented social Media Ontology) is an ontology for describing the information about Social Media focusing on the User Perspective.
